  <subsection xml:id="subsec-Hawaii">
    <title>Hawaiʻi</title>
    <p>
Wanting to revive wayfinding in Hawaiʻi, Nainoa Thompson traveled to the island 
of Satawal in the Federated States of Micronesia to learn from navigator Mau Piailug, 
who affectionately became known as Papa Mau. Thompson adopted the paafu, resulting in 
the Hawaiian <em>Star Compass</em><idx><h>Star Compass</h><h>Hawaiian</h></idx>, also known as the 
<em>Kūkuluokalani</em><idx><h>Kūkuluokalani</h></idx> (<xref ref="star-compass-32-compass-rose">Figure</xref>).
</p>

